prompt: The website whitehouse.gov is the official website of the U.S. Presidency. In which of the following circumstances would this be a good source of information?
feedback: Most websites include a way to contact the company or organization that runs the website. Whitehouse.gov includes a way to send a comment or question to the White House. A news or polling organization would be a better source for information about polls. If you wanted to start a community organization, a website where you could connect with other people in your community would be a better option. A historical website would be a better source of information about Abraham Lincoln’s presidency.
